        <odd id="ref17">
            <head>Early American History Note</head>
            <p>This manuscript essay from 1832 was written by Charles Trevelyan, the governor of Madras. Broken into eleven sections, he outlines the ways in which imperial governments can force assimilation and acculturation through state policies and institutions in India.</p>
